where Sharon Baumgold and Steven Berger attended his classes. "You'd expect 
Yiddish to be a moribund language and only older people to speak it," says 
attorney Baumgold, "but that's obviously not true. It can't be dying if we 
speak it." SANDRA TATUM / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
