<HEAD>Experts in Magazine Survey Call Bronx Zoo Best</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: For release at 6 p.m. EST; Time set by source.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zoo professionals and animal rights activists
consider the Bronx Zoo the best in America, Parade magazine
announced Thursday.
   The magazine said it drew that conclusion from questionnaires and
interviews of 86 people out of 400 who were asked to identify the 10
best and 10 worst zoos.
   After the Bronx Zoo, whose formal name is New York Zoological
Park, the best zoos were, alphabetically:
   Arizona-Sonora Desert Museum, Tucson, Ariz.; Audubon Park and
Zoological Garden, New Orleans; Chicago Zoological Park, Brookfield,
Ill.; Cincinnati Zoo and Botanical Garden; Los Angeles Zoo; National
Zoological Park, Washington, D.C.; St. Louis Zoological Park; San
Diego Zoo; and Woodland Park Zoological Gardens, Seattle, Wash.
   The 10 worst, also alphabetically:
   Brevard Zoological Park, Melbourne, Fla.; Franklin Park Zoo,
Boston; Glen Oak Zoo, Peoria, Ill.; Knowland Park Oakland Zoo,
Oakland, Calif.; Nay Aug Zoo, Scranton, Pa.; Prospect Park Zoo, New
York City; Saunookes Bear Land, Cherokee, N.C.; Space Farms Zoo and
Museum, Sussex, N.J.; Terry Lou Zoo, Scotch Plains, N.J.; and Walk
in the Wild, Spokane, Wash.
   The Franklin Park, Prospect Park and Nay Aug zoos also were on
the worst list in a Parade magazine rating five years ago.
   The Prospect Park Zoo in Brooklyn is being taken over by the
Bronx Zoo and is to be modernized and upgraded.
</TEXT>
